All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Display
    This class is used to display the content of the odometer variables (x, y, Theta)
    Launcher
    Abstraction of the Launcher mounted on the robot.
    LightLocalizer
    Contains the implementation of Light Localization and abstracts the logic behind it to one method call, which is localize.
    Main
    Starting point of the code.
    Navigation
    Navigates the robot depending on given coordinates avoids obstacles and resumes navigation
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    Resources.Point
    Represents a coordinate point on the competition map grid.
    Resources.Region
    Represents a region on the competition map grid, delimited by its lower-left and upper-right corners (inclusive).
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    Contains the implementation of Ultrasonic Localization and abstracts the logic to behind it to one method call, which is localize.
    UltrasonicPoller
    Simple UltrasonicPoller that samples the US sensor and method returns true when obstacle is detected
